      • metadata

        public java.lang.String metadata(java.lang.String metadataPath)
                          throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from interface: GceComputeService

        Gets metadata on the current running machine (call to http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/instance/xxx).

        For example, you can retrieve network information by replacing xxx with:

        • `hostname` when we need to resolve the host name
        • `network-interfaces/0/ip` when we need to resolve private IP
        Specified by:
        metadata in interface GceComputeService
        Parameters:
        metadataPath - path to metadata information
        Returns:
        extracted information (for example a hostname or an IP address)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - in case metadata URL is not accessible
